				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">That and <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">/</tt> is a fairly expensive operation that's hard to pipeline. A multiplication by 8 or by 33/4 might allow more throughput on an old Pentium than a formula involving a division by 31.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
