					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">DRW wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Then I've read some stuff about replicating the top three bits into the bottom three bits to get to the full range. Which sounds totally random and nonsensical to me. Why should you ever do this? In how far do the upper and the lower bits have any connection to each other to ever justify this kind of behavior?</div><br />They have a connection with each other because you are doing a division in which the denominator will always generate a repeating fraction in decimal.  The same also applies to any number base system (binary, in this case).  The repeating values to the right of the decimal point will use values from the left of the decimal.  (I explained it a bit more in this post: <!-- l --><a class="postlink-local" href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?f=5&amp;t=12739&amp;p=146789#p146789">viewtopic.php?f=5&amp;t=12739&amp;p=146789#p146789</a><!-- l --> )</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.chrismcovell.com">http://www.chrismcovell.com</a><!-- m --></div>
